OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782915514
OL,3,CCan you save any money as energy price
OL,4,Ccap rises by 13%?
OL,6,FAnother short-term action you could
OL,7,Ftake to beat the July 1 price rise is
OL,8,Fto take a meter reading today and
OL,9,Fsubmit it to your supplier to prevent
OL,10,Fthem from billing your cheaper spring
OL,11,Fenergy usage at the higher July rates.
OL,13,FPaying via monthly direct debit rather
OL,14,Fthan cash or cheque costs around #140
OL,15,Fless each year, according to Money
OL,16,FSaving Expert.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
