OL,3,CCan you save any money as energy price
OL,4,Ccap rises by 13%?
OL,6,FReducing your thermostat by just 1C
OL,7,Fcan slash your overall bill by up to
OL,8,F10%.
OL,10,FAny new chancellor will have energy
OL,11,Fbills at the top of their in-tray, but
OL,12,Fearlier this year Chancellor Rachel
OL,13,FReeves said earlier this year she
OL,14,Fwould consider some form of support in
OL,15,Fthe autumn if necessary and if energy
OL,16,Fprices remain high.
OL,18,FEven though energy bills may not go up
OL,19,Ffurther in October, many will face a
OL,20,Fpayment shock in the winter months
OL,21,Funless prices come down.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
