OL,3,CCan you save any money as energy price
OL,4,Ccap rises by 13%?
OL,6,FFigures earlier this week from Ofgem
OL,7,Fshowed debt owed to energy suppliers
OL,8,Freached a record high of #4.79 billion
OL,9,Fin the three months to March ` a 5%
OL,10,Fincrease on the last quarter and 15%
OL,11,Fhigher year on year.
OL,13,FWhile July's higher prices will be
OL,14,Fcushioned by warmer weather and lower
OL,15,Fhousehold energy use, the October cap
OL,16,Fwill land as people switch their
OL,17,Fheating back on and will have a
OL,18,Fgreater impact on household finances.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
