CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782915514
OL,3,CCan you save any money as energy price
OL,4,Ccap rises by 13%?
OL,6,FHe added: "October bills always hit
OL,7,Fharder than July's because people are
OL,8,Fturning their heating on again and
OL,9,Fthis year that coincides with a
OL,10,Fdifficult geopolitical backdrop.
OL,12,F"The new prime minister will face real
OL,13,Fpressure to act on support for
OL,14,Fvulnerable households but the harder
OL,15,Fquestion is what comes after that `
OL,16,Fcurrently we are in a perpetual cycle
OL,17,Fof global shocks, high bills and short-
OL,18,Fterm fixes.
OL,26,@nD@KOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
