CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1782915514
OL,3,CCan you save any money as energy price
OL,4,Ccap rises by 13%?
OL,6,F"More permanent measures like social
OL,7,Ftariffs, moving levies into general
OL,8,Ftaxation, or removing VAT on energy
OL,9,Fbills would take some of the pressure
OL,10,Foff bill-payers but there is no firm
OL,11,Fsteer that these options are being
OL,12,Factively pursued by government at the
OL,13,Fmoment."
OL,15,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,16,Four political experts are across all
OL,17,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,18,Fto the latest episode below...
